						<div class="postbody">Okay, this may seem dumb, but when you say 113.666667 CPU cycles per scanline, do you mean per vblank? Okay, I don't think you do, I may sound stupid, because I know what I'm talking about more than it seems, but! I did a short test with the hello world program I made, and! I stored 0 in vbl_count before my endless loop. In my code I said this:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lda #$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; sta vbl_count<br />loop:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lda vbl_count<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cmp #0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; beq keepinc<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; jmp loop<br /><br />keepinc:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; inc stuff<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; jmp loop<br /></div>
<br />
<br />and stuff ended up being #$72, which is 114! Which is most likely the number you're refering to: 113.666667, just the NES rounds it up because it doesn't do precise decimal things. But am I right about what I said? I think I am, I may be stupid, I don't know.</div>

